<section id="master-overlay" class="master-overlay">
  <section class="master-overlay-parent">
    <header>
      <h2>This is a master-overlay</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="master-overlay-content">
      <p>
        Master overlays are the master portion of a master-detail view which is overlayed over the
        main content view.  For the EDSC, this typically contains the collection facets, search results,
        and pinned collections, overlayed over the main map view.
      </p>
      <p>
        Master overlays contain two sections, styled as vertical columns.  The left column is the
        "master-overlay-parent", the right is the "master-overlay-main".  They differ mostly
        in size, background color, and the ability to close the parent while keeping the main
        area visible.
      </p>
      <p>
        Master overlays have a static header area and a scrollable body which stretches the vertical
        height of the main portion of the page
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
