            <i class="fa fa-circle-o-left"></i> Back navigation
          </a>
        </nav>
        <header class="with-options">
          <h2>This is the master overlay main area <small class="version-label">VERSION 1</small> </h2>
          <p>
            It contains an example of a panel-list.  Panel lists are used to show item summaries as
            tiles / panels (as opposed to a columnar view).  Typically, panel-list-items will have thumbnails
            or placeholders, some obvious title, some descriptive text, and some actions to perform on the
            item.  Panel lists are used most often for collection views.
          </p>
          <div class="master-overlay-global-actions actions">
